# =============================================================================
# WARNINGS & PRECAUTIONS (Critical Safety Information)
# =============================================================================
WARNINGS:
  General_Warnings:
    - Start with lowest concentration
    - Build up slowly over months
    - Expect purging period (don't panic)
    - System is more vulnerable during use
    - Always use with moisturizer (context preservation)
    - Always use with sunscreen (security protection)
    - Can cause initial worsening (temporary)
    - Discontinue if severe reactions (critical failures)
    
  Retinol_Specific:
    - Apply only at night (off-peak)
    - Increases photosensitivity (vulnerability)
    - May cause dryness (information loss)
    - May cause irritation (team friction)
    - Not for pregnant systems (major migrations)
    - Can bleach fabrics (data corruption if misused)
    - Store in cool, dark place (secure repository)
    
  Tretinoin_Specific:
    - Prescription required
    - Expert supervision mandatory
    - Intense purging expected
    - High risk of side effects
    - Not for first-time users
    - Requires comprehensive support
    - Rollback plan essential
    - Business continuity planning required

# =============================================================================
# CONTRAINDICATIONS (When NOT to Use)
# =============================================================================
CONTRAINDICATIONS:
  Absolute:
    - System actively failing (repair first)
    - Major migration in progress (too risky)
    - Team at capacity (no bandwidth for transformation)
    - Business critical period (earnings, holidays)
    - No rollback capability (too dangerous)
    - Insufficient monitoring (blind transformation)
    - No expert oversight (for prescription strength)
    
  Relative:
    - Sensitive legacy systems (start very gentle)
    - Recently hired team (wait for onboarding)
    - Recent major incident (wait for stability)
    - Pending audit or compliance (wait until after)
    - Limited budget (transformation needs resources)
    - Resistant stakeholders (need buy-in first)

# =============================================================================
# COMBINATION THERAPY (The Retinol Routine)
# =============================================================================
PERFECT_ROUTINE:
  Evening_Transformation_Routine:
    1. Oil Cleanser (deep technical debt analysis)
    2. Water Cleanser (code cleanup and formatting)
    3. Exfoliant (2x/week - pruning and optimization)
    4. THIS PRODUCT (Retinol architecture transformation)
    5. Moisturizer (context and memory preservation)
    6. Occlusive (seal in changes with documentation)
    
  Morning_Protection_Routine:
    1. Gentle Cleanser (input validation)
    2. Antioxidant Serum (monitoring and alerting)
    3. Moisturizer (memory management)
    4. SUNSCREEN (security - CRITICAL after retinol)
    
  Weekly_Intensive:
    1. Exfoliant (pruning session)
    2. Mask (deep optimization)
    3. Retinol (intensive transformation)
    4. Overnight Treatment (batch processing)
    
  DO_NOT_Combine_With:
    - Other strong exfoliants same night (over-optimization)
    - Benzoyl peroxide (conflicting approaches)
    - Vitamin C in same routine (instability)
    - High strength AHA/BHA (too much at once)

# =============================================================================
# SANDWICH METHOD (For Sensitive Systems)
# =============================================================================
SANDWICH_METHOD:
  Technique:
    1. Moisturizer (context preservation layer)
    2. Wait 20 minutes (stabilize)
    3. Retinol (transformation layer)
    4. Wait 20 minutes (absorb)
    5. Moisturizer again (sealing layer)
    
  Benefits:
    - Reduces irritation (lower risk)
    - Buffers transformation (gentler)
    - Better tolerated (less purging)
    - Slower results (worth the trade-off)
    
  When_To_Use:
    - Sensitive legacy systems
    - Risk-averse organizations
    - First-time retinol users
    - During stressful periods
    - When team capacity limited

